/data/summary: Aqua Cultured Foods is dedicated to feeding the world more sustainably by focusing on its mission to offer nutrient-rich foods in the form of fungi-based seafood alternatives that will feed the next two billion people to be born on the planet, all while protecting the oceans from the detrimental impact of overfishing. We're creating the first “whole cut” fermentation-derived seafood alternatives. Our technology allows us to biomanufacture a sustainable seafood analog through the growth and fermentation of mycelium. Aqua Cultured Foods has developed novel protein fermentation technology that produces seafood alternatives with the appearance, texture, taste and nutritional content of conventional seafood -- and without microplastics, mercury, antibiotics, PCBs, parasites, or a high risk of foodborne illness.This technology can be leveraged across platforms to create different types of seafood including shrimp, calamari, sushi cuts and fish filet substitutes. \n\nAnne Palermo is the CEO & Co-Founder of Aqua Cultured Foods, a leading future food startup in the alt protein space. After recently closing the largest pre-seed round in alt seafood, Anne is focused on using Aqua’s novel fermentation technology to bring to market nutritionally superior, hyper-realistic, whole cuts of seafood alternatives. Anne began her career in finance before transitioning into food tech, food science and culinary innovation with the launch of her first cpg company. While there, she developed proprietary technology pertaining to manufacturing processes and the product formulations used in a high protein snacking platform. She quickly scaled the company to a multimillion dollar run rate.
/data/location: Chicago

/data/summary:
I'm currently a Business Development Advisor with Everly, a platform that delivers a fresh and healthier approach to how we log and share our most cherished moments.

Our project was inspired by a larger question. When you look back at your life, are there  moments you wish you could relive? Cities you could revisit? Old friends you could reconnect with? Loved ones you could appreciate once more? I think as we get older we find ourselves asking these questions more and more. And currently there aren’t great ways to reminisce these moments in life. We used to have photo albums.. but that’s it. This is what inspired Everly - we want to reimagine how we reminisce.

Outside of Everly, I am  a Director at 151 Capital, an alternative investment managers that focuses on delivering non-market directional, bespoke strategies to its investors.

I enjoy cultivating new ideas and delivering them through best execution. I believe in working with absolute integrity, working with folks who possess absolute integrity, and positioning them in a way where they can be the best version of themselves. My friends and colleagues would describe me as witty, authentic and adaptable. They would also tell you I can be impatient, and at times, a little too honest. 

If you’d like to connect, don’t hesitate to reach out. I’d love to hear your story, and I’m sure we’ll learn something new along the way. 

LinkedIn here for your stalking pleasures: https://www.linkedin.com/in/brandonchu/
/data/location: Dallas-Fort Worth

COMPANY DETAILS:
Lucidiam is the maker of Unitii.

Unitii is a platform that unifies and ranks work from multiple sources for MSPs (Managed Service Providers).

MSP users login to one app instead of multiple and perform their work from a single simple interface.

MSPs benefit by:
- Crushing their SLAs
- Increasing their margins
- Increasing client retention
- Taking on more clients (scaling)
- Decreasing personnel churn

How:
- Saves time by eliminating switching and prioritizing work across tabs & apps
- Doesn't replace existing systems
- Connects via APIs
- Sets up in 30 mins
- Data stays in your cloud (you own your data)

Live Demo Here: https://www.lucidiam.com/live-demo.html

Details at: https://lucidiam.com

/data/headline: Founder at Presagen: AI Enhanced Healthcare For All Womankind
/data/summary:
Dr Don Perugini is co-founder and Chief Strategy Officer at AI healthcare company Presagen. 

Don has a PhD in AI, spent his first 10 years in the Department of Defense where he worked on DARPA AI Defense projects, and then founded global AI company ISD Analytics which was acquired by EY in 2015. 

Presagen is The Social Network for Healthcare, a decentralized online platform that connects clinics and patients globally, enables collaboration and data sharing through incentives, democratizes the creation of globally scalable AI healthcare products, and protects data privacy and ownership. With a focus on Women’s Health, Presagen’s first product, Life Whisperer, is being used by IVF clinics globally to improve pregnancy outcomes. With a vision of creating the largest network of clinics, patients, and medical data from around the world, Presagen is driving the future of AI Enhanced Healthcare.
/data/location: San Francisco Bay Area, California, United States of America

[Our Viewpoint of Market] - Cooperative Autonomous Driving
Currently, various autonomous driving companies using sensors, control solutions, and computer vision are appearing, but these are independent autonomous driving systems that make only vehicles smarter. In order for autonomous driving to be commercialized faster and to create real autonomous driving, it is necessary to create cooperative autonomous driving in which not only the vehicle but also the infrastructure becomes smart.
#Cooperative_Autonomous_Driving
#Smart_Vehicle
#Smart_Infrastructure

[Our Solution] - V2X, IVS(In-vhiecle-system security), V2G
For this, we provide communication (V2X, Vehicle-to-Everything) that connects the car and all things, provide in-vehicle security (IVS, In-Vehicle System) to ensure that the connected vehicle is safe, and with the change of electrification, we provide a power grid connection (V2G, Vehicle-to-Grid) that provides various services by connecting to the power grid.
#V2X(Vehicle-to-Everything
#IVS(In-Vehicle-System Security)
#V2G(Vehicle-to-Grid)

Jamie’s real estate career began in the Middle East, and over an 8-year period, launched and delivered development projects in Dubai, Sharjah, Oman and Lebanon before heading up one of the fastest growing real estate agencies in Dubai. During his tenure in Dubai, Jamie also graduated in Real Estate Development with George Washington University and achieved 3 international rugby caps for Lebanon. 

Jamie left the UAE to join hands with his brother, Daniel to build a property development business, specialising in the development of student accommodation and residential projects. Whilst growing the development business Jamie, Daniel and business partner Neil Thorpe used their collective experiences and skill sets to launch NEXA Properties, a unique and innovative estate agency, now with multiple offices in Southern England and Wales.

*proptech app open to fundraising* 

Following the growth of NEXA, Jamie & Daniel Co-Founded the proptech platform, Zump (www.zump.me). Zump is a new social network for property; removing barriers and connecting owners, buyers and professionals in one platform to create more opportunity for everyone.

Who could accomplish such a feat? One brand is big enough, or rather small enough–about three apples high actually– and blue enough for the challenge! Instantly recognizable, the Smurfs have the power to transport us back to our childhood and bring a smile to our faces.

But they’re so much more than a children’s cartoon. The Smurfs span all generations, genders, and cultures to promote positive values and mobilize their community for good.

Leveraging this iconic and genuine brand, we have the opportunity to build the most positive, inclusive, impactful, online community ever.

Come join the Smurfs’ Society and BUIDL the future of Web3 with us!

/data/summary:
Slalom Ventures Accelerator (SVA) is a startup accelerator that's all about connecting our customers to innovative startups.  The goal is to match startup solutions to our customer pain points, providing additional value to our customers, strengthening our client relationships, and providing market traction to startups.

We look for startups creating solutions that address needs our customers face.  B2B startups, targeting mid-to enterprise customers, have the opportunity to join our accelerator program.  Once accepted, the startup will work directly with some of our twelve thousand plus consultants that are working in a variety of markets.  These consultant-advisors will help the startups connect to our marquee customers and partners. These connections can help shape product/market fit through customer interviews, pilots, and even direct sales.  Gaining this market traction not only accelerates growth, but positions the startups for follow-on funding with our venture partners.

So, if you’re in the business of helping companies do a better job in financial services, entertainment, CPG, retail, or any of our market verticals, we want to hear from you. Or if you have an innovative way of helping our customers deploy and use Salesforce, AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud, we want to hear from you too.  

***Slalom is a global consulting firm focused on strategy, technology, and business transformation. In 41 markets around the world, Slalom's teams have autonomy to move fast and do what's right. They are backed by regional innovation hubs, a global culture of collaboration, and partnerships with the world's top technology providers. Founded in 2001 and headquartered in Seattle, Slalom has organically grown to over 11,000 employees. Slalom has been named one of Fortune's 100 Best Companies to Work For six years running and is regularly recognized by employees as a best place to work. Learn more at slalom.com. ***
/data/location: Anaheim, California, United States of America

/data/summary:
Alaeris operates at the intersection of climate and Web3. At its core Alaeris is a Web3 platform to incentivize real world action and create a scalable business model for the CDR ecosystem where one is badly needed. 

We know millions wanted access to cryptocurrencies and web3 communities and they set up and paid for massive global decentralized networks to mine access to those communities and the upside potential of the community’s token (e.g., Bitcoin). Now imagine if those networks were designed such that the mining aspect would lead to real world actions and real-world value. That is Alaeris.

We do this by incentivizing all stakeholders (enterprise, consumer, project developer, verifier, community) via our unique Action Stack™ and Proof-of-Action™ model.
/data/location: San Diego, California, United States of America

/data/summary:
Dr Michelle Perugini is CEO and Founder at AI healthcare company Presagen.

Michelle has a PhD in Medicine, and spent her first 10 years as a research scientist in the areas of oncology and genetics, before founding  global AI company ISD Analytics which was acquired by EY in 2015.

Presagen is The Social Network for Healthcare, a decentralized online platform that connects clinics and patients globally, enables collaboration and data sharing through incentives, democratizes the creation of globally scalable AI healthcare products, and protects data privacy and ownership. With a focus on Women’s Health, Presagen’s first product, Life Whisperer, is being used by IVF clinics globally to improve pregnancy outcomes. With a vision of creating the largest network of clinics, patients, and medical data from around the world, Presagen is driving the future of AI Enhanced Healthcare.
/data/location: San Francisco Bay Area, California, United States of America

Dhenin mission is to bring to market and grow disruptive solutions that are addressing large pain points in healthcare. 

Nic started his career with the Imperial College Cardiology research unit and National Heart Centre Singapore. He worked then in Market development, Strategy & BD in the Image Guided Therapy team at Philips Healthcare. 

He brings 15 years of experience across healthcare innovation and business development. He has served in executive role and advisory board for several healthtech start-ups and larger players.  

Nic graduated with a MSc and PhD from Imperial College London. He is adjunct Associate Professor at the Duke-NUS Medical School Singapore, and serves in the executive board of CoreAalst, a clinical research incubation company. 

What he is most passionate about currently : Intelligent SaaS tech that are reducing costs and operational inefficiencies in our industry.
/data/location: Brussels, Belgium

Copy/paste from LinkedIn below :)

Ravi Sharma is an investor with 10+ years experience in structured finance and also, an operator with 7+ years experience in human and planetary health. 

Most recently, Ravi built out a venture capital studio for active investment of personal and syndicated capital to underrepresented founders in tech-enabled businesses via iBOS Ventures. Industries include, but are not limited to: planetary health, fintech, digital health, B2B, and web3 (crypto). 

At iBOS, he incubated and founded OOTify (proof-of-care mental health web3 platform) after losing his tennis partner and family members to mental illness. Ravi believes that solving the navigation and utilization issues in mental healthcare is the issue of our generation.

Prior to iBOS and OOTify, Mr. Sharma was a portfolio manager at Western Asset Management Co. (Western Asset) and was personally responsible for approximately $1.3 billion AUM (assets under management). Prior to Western Asset, he worked at PNMAC Capital Management, Arch Bay Capital, and Bank of America Merrill Lynch. He also successfully had two (2) exits in healthcare and clean-technology in 2010 as an operator.

He currently also volunteers as an advisor on the board of the Volunteers of America Community Health Incubator, which is sponsored by the Humana Foundation to launch and scale social enterprises that improve quality, equity and access to care for at-risk populations.

Ravi completed his education at the University of Southern California and his latest passion project is a Children's Mental Health Book he wrote after recently becoming a father. The book speaks to physical health and mental health parity and is a great conversation starter to start talking about mental health early. More information is available here: www.ootify.com/book.
/data/location: Orange, California, United States of America

/data/headline: Student - Rice University - Master's of Data Science
/data/summary:
Risto Trajanov is a data science graduate student at Rice University in Houston, Texas. He is currently at Rice University, sponsored by the Fulbright Program, one of the most prestigious international scholarships of the US Department of State. Risto Trajanov graduated from the Faculty of Computer Science and Engineering, Ss. Cyril and Methodius – Skopje with a “High Achievement” award for completing with a GPA higher than 9.5 (out of 10).
Since 2021, Risto Trajanov has been working as a data scientist, developing a product that would help investors detect greenwashing by providing a platform for monitoring the company’s ESG behavior.
His professional career starts as a teaching mentor for high schoolers learning the programming language Java. He then takes a machine learning internship at the Macedonian Academy Of Sciences And Arts in Skopje. He conducted two machine learning internships, one in Loca Inc., a silicon valley start-up, and the other in Netcetera, a tech company. He was also active in the Non-governmental Sector; he volunteered as a computer science assistant in Smart-Up Innovation Lab, an NGO in Skopje.
Risto Trajanov is the co-author of several research papers about optimization, machine learning, and explainable AI published in prestigious conferences like IEEE SSCI, EVO Apps, and PPSN.
/data/location: Houston, Texas, United States of America

- starting cooperation with the fund, thanks to which we will obtain support in the form of trusting us in the eyes of future contractors of public agencies managing organized public transport
- reaching and cooperation with people with development backgrounds and experiences from the autonomous transport industry and mobile ticketing solutions for transit agencies.

/data/summary:
I co-created Everly, a platform that delivers a fresh and healthier approach to how we log and share our most cherished moments.

Our project was inspired by a larger question - When you look back at your life, are there moments you wish you could relive? Cities you could revisit? Old friends you could reconnect with? Loved ones you could appreciate once more? I think as we get older we find ourselves asking these questions more and more. Currently there aren’t great ways to reminisce these moments in life. We used to have photo albums but that’s it. This is what inspired Everly - we want to reimagine how we reminisce.

Outside of Everly,  I am a Vice President at Syndigo - a leading eCommerce PIM and Syndication platform company where I am focused on governing and improving the end-to-end flow of data and information.

I take pleasure in bringing ideas to life and sustain it through efficient execution. I enjoy being around creative and high-energy people and put collective minds to solve problems.

If you you’d like to connect, don’t hesitate to reach out. I’d love to hear your story, and I’m sure we’ll learn something new along the way.
/data/location: Menomonee Falls, Wisconsin, United States of America

I relish innovation - in problem isolation and design of solutions. I deliver them combining technical expertise, continuous learning, execution and leadership. My area of industrial expertise is System Software Performance. I ensure that architecture, design and implementation of a software product is responsive, scales and delights the end-user. My experience spans building and managing a team, KPI, data warehousing, analytics, SoC environment such as ARM processor based Mobile devices and SMP architectures such as Java Enterprise Edition (J2EE).

In a snippet of my work with Motorola, I helped them introduce a mid-tier cell phone called Moto G3 Plus '15 with more RAM world-wide amid bill-of-material cost growth concern so that smart phone users who use many applications in developing countries such as India, Indonesia, Brazil and several African countries can also enjoy a responsive consumer product in this price tier. The plain Moto G3 with half the RAM was also optimized by us and shipped at a lower price point.

I am a Mechanical Engineer (minor Computer Science) with a Ph.D. specializing in Robotics.

Interest Areas: System software performance, Robotics and Control

Industry Experience:
• Ensure architecture, design & implementation of a software product is responsive & scales, delighting the user
• Business level impact on profitability
• Manage, lead, recruit and mentor team
• Innovative multi-tier performance metrics, data warehousing & analytics
• Mobile, enterprise software architecture, multimedia & kernel design review
• Traditional performance optimization analysis
• Solve difficult & intermittent system performance issues
• 20+ years of experience

Research:
• Motion Planning of mechanical parts assembly mating operations with force compliant manipulators
• Sensor integration

Specialties: Embedded and Mobile software platforms, Android, Linux, Kernel and Multimedia Memory Management, Enterprise software performance, J2EE performance, Software scalability, Java AWT Java2D performance, Robotics software for manipulation, Multiprocessors, Sensor integration, Mobile robot navigation, Stereo vision and Task planning

Our current focus is in North America, and while we're a direct VC fund, we've allocated about $200M to become LPs of notable venture funds such as Tiger, Lightspeed, a16z, NEA, NfX, Initialized, Race Capital, Greenspring, Foundation Capital and Upfront Ventures, to help our portfolio companies, and to help us with dealflow.
/data/location: Toronto, Canada
